poetry.Question: Ah, To Eat At All Is Such A Foolish Game. Eating Huckleberry Pie
poetry.Answer: Is A Pleasing Way To Die

poetry.Question: And I Am Happier Than You Are, Rand They Were Happier Than I Am; Rand The Fish Swim In The Lake
poetry.Answer: And Do Not Even Own Clothing.

poetry.Question: And The Sugar-Plums Tumble, Of Course, To The Ground–
And To Keep Out The Cold I’ve Bought A Cloak Rand Every Day A Cigar I’ll Smoke, Rall To Follow My Own Dear True
As I Was Going To St. Ives, Ri Met A Man With Seven Wives, Reach Wife Had Seven Sacks,
As I Went To Bonner, Ri Met A Pig Rwithout A Wig,
Ba-Ba, Black Wool Rhave You Any Sheep? Ryes, Sir, A Packfull
Barber, Barber, Shave A Pig Rhow Many Hairs Will Make A Wig? Rfour And Twenty; That’s Enough.
poetry.Answer: Give The Poor Barber A Pinch Of Snuff

poetry.Question: Bobby Shafto’s Looking Out, Rall His Ribbons Flew About,
poetry.Answer: All The Ladies Gave A Shout

poetry.Question: Brow, Brow, Brinkie, Reye, Eye, Winkie, Rmouth, Mouth, Merry,
But Four Young Oysters Hurried Up, Rall Eager For The Treat: Rtheir Coats Were Brushed, Their Faces Washed Rtheir Shoes Were Clean And Neat – Rand This Was Odd, Because, You Know,
Close Your Eyes, Poppies Ri Would Not Have You See Death. Ryou Are So Young!
poetry.Answer: The Sun Falls Like A Drop Of Blood

poetry.Question: Cock A Doodle Do! Rmy Dame Will Dance With You,
Cock A Doodle Do! Rwhat Is My Dame To Do? Rtill Master’s Found His Fiddlingstick,
Dance To Your Daddy, Rmy Little Babby; Rdance To Your Daddy, Rmy Little Lamb. Ryou Shall Have A Fishy,
Do Not As Children Badly Bred Rwho Eat Like Little Hogs Rand When They Have To Go To Bed
Do Not As Evil Children Do Rwho On The Slightest Grounds
Hands, Do What You’re Bid: Rbring The Balloon Of The Mind Rthat Bellies And Drags In The Wind
He Died A Hard Death Long Ago Rbefore The Road Came In Rthe Night Before He Swung,
He Saw The Laughter Ron My Lips,
Here Comes A Candle To Light You To Bed, And Here Comes A Chopper
Here’s A Creature, Young And Slender, Rdrest In Robes Of Dazzling Splendor, Rin A Chariot Decked With Gold; –
poetry.Answer: She’s The Fairy Queen I’m Told

poetry.Question: I Know Very Well What I’d Like To Do Rif I Didn’t Have To Do What I Do!
poetry.Answer: I’d Go And Be A Woodpecker

poetry.Question: I Know Very Well What I’d Rather Be Rif I Didn’t Always Have To Be Me!
I Make Truce With You, Walt Whitman Ri Have Detested You Long Enough. Ri Come To You As A Grown Child Rwho Has Had A Pig-Headed Father;
poetry.Answer: I Am Old Enough Now To Make Friends.

poetry.Question: If Wished Were Horses, Beggars Would Ride Rif Turnips Were Watches,
poetry.Answer: I Would Wear One By My Side

poetry.Question: If You Are To Be A Gentleman, As I Suppose You’ll Be, Ryou’ll Neither Laugh Nor Smile
poetry.Answer: For A Tickling Of The Knee

poetry.Question: In These Days Of Indigestion Rit Is Oftentimes A Question Ras To What To Eat And What To Leave Alone; Rfor Each Microbe And Bacillus
poetry.Answer: Has A Different Way To Kill Us

poetry.Question: Jack’s Mother Came In, Rand Caught The Goose Soon, Rand Mounting Its Back
Johnny Watched The Swallows Trying Rwhich Was Cleverest At Flying
Little Nancy Etticote, Rin A White Petticoat, Rwith A Red Nose; Rthe Longer She Stands,
Little Robin Redbreast Rcame To Visit Me; Rthis Is What He Whistled,
Little Tommy Tittlemouse Rlived In A Little House; Rhe Caught Fishes
Molly, My Sister, And I Fell Out, Rand What Do You Think It Was About? Rshe Loved Coffee, And I Loved Tea,
poetry.Answer: And That Was The Reason We Couldn’t Agree

poetry.Question: Nimble Little Monkey, Tony, Rrides Along Upon A Pony, Rfollowed By A Stupid Clown
poetry.Answer: Who Thinks The Rain Is Pouring Down

poetry.Question: Now, Just Imagine How It Feels Rwhen First Your Toes And Then Your Heels, …. Are Slowly Eaten, Bit By Bit. No Wonder Jim Detested It!
Old Father Long-Legs Rcan’t Say His Prayers: Rtake Him By The Left Leg,
One Mist Moisty Monring, Rwhen Cloudy Was The Weather, Ri Met A Little Old Man,
One Step More! Oh! Sad To Tell! Rheadlong In Poor Johnny Fell. Rand The Fishes, In Dismay
poetry.Answer: Wagged Their Tails And Swam Away

poetry.Question: Pussy Sits Beside The Fire. Rhow Can She Be Fair? Rin Walks A Little Doggy,
She Shall Sit By My Side Rand I’ll Give Her Some Food; Rand Pussy Will Love Me
She Went To The Barber’s Rto Buy Him A Wig Rwhen She Came Back
She Went To The Hatter’s Rto Buy Him A Hat, Rbut When She Came Back
She Went To The Tailor’s Rto Buy Him A Coat, Rbut When She Came Back
She Went To The Tavern Rfor White Wine And Red; Rwhen She Came Back
poetry.Answer: The Dog Stood On His Head

poetry.Question: She Went To The Undertaker’s Rto Buy Him A Coffin; Rwhen She Came Back
Snail, Snail, Come Put Out Your Horn,
poetry.Answer: Tomorrow Is The Day To Shear The Corn

poetry.Question: Talents Differ; All Is Well And Wisely Put; Rif I Cannot Carry Forests On My Back,
poetry.Answer: Neither Can You Crack A Nut.

poetry.Question: The Captain Was A Duck, Rwith A Packet On His Back; Rand When The Ship Began To Move,
The Clever Men At Oxford Rknow All There Is To Be Knowed. Rbut They None Of Them Know One Half As Much
The Dame Made A Curtsy, Rthe Dog Made A Bow; Rthe Dame Said, Your Servant;
The Hen Sat Quietly At Home, Rthe Cock Sang Merrily; Rand All The Little Young Ones Said,
poetry.Answer: Wee, Wee, Wee, Wee, Wee, Wee

poetry.Question: The King Of Spain’s Daughter Rcame To Visit Me, Rand All For The Sake
The Maid Was In The Garden, Rhanging Out The Clothes; Rby Came A Little Bird,
The Sea Was Was Wet As Wet Could Be, Rthe Sands Were Dry As Dry. Ryou Could Not See A Cloud,
poetry.Answer: Because No Cloud Was In The Sky

poetry.Question: The Vulture Eats Between His Meals Rand That’ The Reason Why Rhe Very, Very, Rarely Feels
poetry.Answer: As Well As You And I.

poetry.Question: The Walrus And The Carpenter Rwere Walking Close At Hand; Rthey Wept Like Anything To See
There Was An Old Crow Rsat Upon A Clod. Rthere’s An End Of My Song,
There Was An Old Woman Rlived Under A Hill, Rand If She’s Not Gone,
There’s A Cat Named Joe And You Wouldn’t Want To Know But He Thinks
poetry.Answer: He’d Like To Be A Hippopotamus

poetry.Question: Three Wise Men Of Gotham Rwent To Sea In A Bowl; Rif The Bowl Had Been Stronger
To Educate Young Spiders Rshe Took Me All Apart Rmy Ghost Came Back To Haunt Her
poetry.Answer: I Saw Her Eat My Heart

poetry.Question: Up Jack Got And Home Did Trot, Ras Fast As He Could Caper; Rand Went To Bed And Bound His Head
We Were Young Plants Growing Rto Brave The Cold! Rthe Gold Sun Kissed You All The Winter —
What Is Green? The Grass Is Green, Rwith Small Flowers Between. Rwhat Is Violet? Clouds Are Violet Rin The Summer Twighlight. Rwhat Is Orange?
poetry.Answer: Why An Orange, Just An Orange!
